result.name: Snapper Soup Restaurant

reviews.text: Walking back to my hotel, spotted this place. Stepped in just before closing time. Waiter was friendly and told me it was now last orders. There was a lot of items on the menu, mostly soup and broths in iron pots, served either with udon or rice. And you can add extra meat/seafood items, too. I chose the oyster soup with rice, added cuttlefish balls with ink. It was excellent. Had side order of gyoza, was just ok. Overall, quite satisfying. Will be back next time.
Famous for their snapper soup base udon, good value
The soup isnt that great and a bit overpriced
The fish soup is a bit salty and thick, but still very good!

I went at 2pm when the tea time started, interestingly they don’t serve their signature fish-based udon during tea time. Tried the pork bone based udon with teriyaki chicken, the soup tastes sweet and nourishing, the chicken is tender, the only bad thing is I found a hair in the soup udon... It’s only $48 without service charge so maybe we can’t ask for too much. Another disappointing fact: cash only! It’s hard to believe it’s 2019 but still many restaurants in HK accept cash only.

result.name: 鯛魚魚湯專門店

reviews.text: 魚湯烏冬幾好食👌

同區抵食嘅下午茶
一餸配沙律菜、一碗豬骨湯烏冬加熱飲$48-$50
湯冇味精，餸份量多👍🏼
但座位好迫，必須搭枱，人多時餐廳內會比較嘈，還有冷氣不足。
總結：食物👍🏼環境👎🏼
魚湯烏冬好味，但吉列豬扒一般

Walking back to my hotel, spotted this place. Stepped in just before closing time. Waiter was friendly and told me it was now last orders. There was a lot of items on the menu, mostly soup and broths in iron pots, served either with udon or rice. And you can add extra meat/seafood items, too. I chose the oyster soup with rice, added cuttlefish balls with ink. It was excellent. Had side order of gyoza, was just ok. Overall, quite satisfying. Will be back next time.
用心製作，用料新鮮。我不喜歡過量調味，這店正好能做到，店家應無下味精，每次把湯喝清，回家也不會感口渴。對健康有要求的，一試會愛上
